        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the batter and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Grease a 900 g loaf tin and line with baking paper. Beat the butter and sugar until pale and fluffy. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Fold in the flour and baking powder. Stir in the lemon zest, poppyseeds, and milk. Spoon into the tin and level the surface. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until a skewer comes out clean, the surface is pale gold and set, and the loaf pulls slightly from the sides.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Apply the drizzle while hot",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the lemon juice and granulated sugar together in a small bowl. As soon as the cake comes out of the oven, prick the top all over with a skewer. Pour the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "lemon drizzle",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "term": "lemon drizzle",
                  "termId": "cmpbjykho0000skv4w8lzeiua"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " slowly over the hot cake, letting it soak in. Leave in the tin until completely cool before turning out. The drizzle crust forms as it dries.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
